column3: Abdominal segments with laterally projecting tufts of scales on segments II-VII?
column4: Hindtarsus with at least last 2 hindtarsomeres entirely pale?
column5: Hindtarsomere 5 mainly or entirely dark, hindtarsomere 4 white
column7: Wing entirely dark or with pale spots confined to costa and vein 1
column8: Wing with at least 1 pale spot on basal 0.5 of costa
column11: Wing with pale interruption in 3rd main dark area (preapical dark spot) of vein 1, sometimes fused with preceding pale area
column12: Wing with 2 pale spots on upper branch of vein 5
column13: Wing almost entirely dark, costa without pale spots
column15: Hindtarsomeres 1 and 2 with definite pale and dark rings in addition to apical pale bands
column16: Hindtarsomeres 3 and 4 all white or narrowly dark basally, 5 all dark or at least basal 0.5 dark
column17: Hindtarsomere 5 and about apical 0.5 of 4 pale
column19: Maxillary palpus very shaggy and unbanded or with 1-4 irregular narrow pale bands
column20: Maxillary palpus with 1-4 pale bands; apex of hindtibia broadly or narrowly pale
column22: Hind tarsomere 1 entirely dark basally or at most with a very narrow band of pale scales not as broad as the width of the tarsomere
column23: Apex of hindtibia with a pale streak 3-5 times as long as broad; apical pale band on hindtarsomere 2 0.13-0.4 length of tarsomere
column25: Maxillary palpus with apical 2 pale bands very broad, speckling on palpus segment 3; 2nd main dark area on wing vein 1 with 2 pale interruptions
column26: 3rd main dark area of wing vein 1 with a pale interruption, sometimes fused with preceding pale spot; scaling on abdomen very scanty, confined to tergum VIII or rarely VII
column27: All tarsi completely dark; wing without pale fringe spots posterior to vein 3
column28: 3rd main dark area of vein 1 with a pale interruption, sometimes fused with preceding pale area
column29: Maxillary palpus with only apex pale
column30: Base of costa with large (presector) pale spot, base of vein 1 pale
column31: Subapical pale spot on costa and wing vein 1 about as long as apical dark spot, fringe spots present opposite veins 3, lower branch of 4 and both branches of 5
column32: Hindtarsomeres 1 to 4 with pale bands overlapping the joints, at least hindtarsomere 5 pale basally
column33: Preaccessory dark spot on wing vein 1 about twice as long as pale spot on either side of it
column34: Basal area of wing vein 1 proximal to 1st main dark area, pale with a broad dark spot
column35: Subapical pale band on maxillary palpus longer than or equal to apical dark band AND 3rd main dark area of costa and vein 1 equal to or shorter than subapical pale spot
column36: Moderate-sized species, wing length more than 3.3 mm
column37: Tip of wing vein 6 dark with no fringe spot
